The filmmaker wants to make a series on different ancient civilizations which will have a total of $n$ episodes. He intends to focus on five ancient civilizations: Egyptian, Roman, Greek, Mayan, and Chinese civilizations. The historian, on the other hand, has managed to gather enough information to make $a$, $b$, $c$, $d$, and $e$ episodes on the Egyptian, Roman, Greek, Mayan, and Chinese civilizations respectively, where $a,b,c,d,e \in \mathbb{Z^+}$. The filmmaker insisted that each civilization must have at least one episode dedicated to it, and no civilization should have more than twice the number of episodes dedicated to any other civilization. Considering these constraints, determine the number of non-negative integer solutions $(x,y,z,w,u)$ for the equation 

\begin{equation}
x + y + z + w + u = n
\end{equation}

where $1\leq x\leq a$, $1\leq y\leq b$, $1\leq z\leq c$, $1\leq w\leq d$, $1\leq u\leq e$, and $x,y,z,w,u \leq 2 \times \min\{x,y,z,w,u\}$.
